<br />

<br />
Doesnt have to be. I played a game where you would cast "create water" while targeting a container based off random number generator it would create some liquid in the container. The containers vary in size and the spell would fill the container whether you had a barrel or a plain waterskin.  The liquids, mostly potable, some not had certain properties. Tea, orange juice, water(funny that),coffee, wine(will get you drunk too),beer,(about 20 more), one was a wine the removed rez effects and was a very rare cast. Grease and oils for "tinkering"(proper translation) were created and an acid for "jewel crafting". if you cast an acid into a container that would be eaten by it, you lost your container. I had a chance to work on the code for that game and was very surprised at what i found.  It could have gotten ugly but good coders write their programs like a good story. It truely is an art.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
