                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Actually there is a simpler way that does not infringe upon the rezing class's terf, so it would have more liklyhood of being accepted. 
<br />

<br />
First, a "permanent illusion other" AA would be useful, to cast on people.  This would produce an icon in their spell window that they could remove or keep, but would last even when they zoned, untill they died or it wore off after several weeks.
<br />

<br />
Second, a "copy form" illusion.  We know this spell exists, we have seen several "impersonators" , the sarnak impersonator being one, another was in the pit in overthere.  Such a spell would involve 2 castings. This spell would only work in the zone it was cast.  First you cast it on the form you want copied into memory. This could be a spider, a dragon, or a for exampe a warrior pc.  The second cast would be on the person recieveing the form.  I could turn myself into a spider or dragon or the exact warrior copied with all their armor, male or female, and look just like them.  
<br />

<br />
In many books you always read about powerful witches cursing thier enemies by turning them into native wildlife.  Why can't some npc's be able to very rarly curse people into say a level 4 spider, that can't be removed and won't let it be removed for say a week real tiem unless removed sooner. They would have to figure out how to remove the curse, and it would have to be more difficult than just geting a remove curse spell from a cleric. Perhaps some interesting quest, exploring some dark cave only a spider could crawl through, or some such unique quest depending on what the witch turned you into. We need witches in EQ. 
<br />

<br />
Third, we need more new players in EQ1.  The newbie zones are deserted, it is not possible even to find groups on low level alts anymore.  SOE should consider giving EQ1 trilogy free to people who subscribe to their other games such as EQ2 so that they can log in and see what happened in the past.  They would still benefit by having more people playing and keeping a steady supply of new people so the old people will still have people to play with.  And they need to add new lore for the new people too..like evil witches in Commonlands that turn you into snakes! 
<br />

<br />
Lillywhite</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
